{"title": "Instant Chat - Patient Related Chat", "body": "Instant Chat - Patient Related Chat\n\nIn article of the Instant Chat, you will learn how to flag a patient in a chat message, open a patient record from the chat message, and how to review the chat history of messages related to that patient from within the patient record.\n\nFlagging a patient name in chat\n\nTo flag a patient name in a chat message, click New to start a new message.\n\n\n\nAdd the name of the user you are sending the message to, and click Patient Name to flag a patient in the message.\n\n\n\nType in a keyword from the patient name to locate the patient, select the patient name and type in the message.\n\nClick Send to send the message to the user.\n\n\n\nWhen the message is delivered to the user, there will be a Patient sub-heading in message. Click the Patient Name to open the patient record.\n\n\n\nThe patient record will open, and there will be a counter on the Dashboard tab, indicating that there is a new message for you related to that patient.\n\nTo view the message, click Dashboard.\n\n\n\nClick Chat to open the messages related to the patient.\n\n\n\nThe message will be displayed at the top of the list, and you can respond to the user that sent the message from the patient record the same way you respond to messages from the home page.\n\nPatient related chat history\n\nTo review the chat history related to a patient, open the patient record and click Dashboard.\n\n\n\nClick Chat History to open the messages related to the patient and view the message history.\n\n\n\n*Note: You will only be able to see the history of messages addressed to you, not the full history of messages addressed to other users.\n\nNeed help?\n1300 103 903\nsupport@medirecords.com"}